reviews.review_text: Smokin 81 Show a must have imho.killer playin>drums>space>wheel>playin reprise.nice spanish theme at the end playin before drums.enjoy the show and thanks to all involved for the show.tasty nugs.

Thanks again, Mr. Charlie Another polished gem from the Shaman of Sound--Charlie Miller.  Your  efforts are not going un-noticed and are VERY APPRECIATED.  This whole show--setlist and performance are top-notch.  No weak spots, IMO.  One note of interest: Check out Bobby as they head into the Playin' Jam...one of a kind!!  Very fine performance this night.

Keep 'em coming! "One note of interest: Check out Bobby as they head into the Playin' Jam...one of a kind!!"

Ha! Indeed.  Bobby spends a minute or two driftin and dreamin'.  I must admit I have not heard of a show where that happens during Playin', before or since.

niceness all around a nice sound a good mix of tunes everyone is there and the Bobby wanderings at the start of Playin are a joy D/L this Stream it whatever strikes your fancy

Peace:Skippy
Best of 1981 This 2nd set is incredible - short, but sweet - a real gem...Bobby does do this adlib on Playin' at Red Rocks - the only other time I have ever heard him talk at that point of playin'
Drums They are so tight during that

Cool over all show The first set is very good. They get right down to it with a  hot Minglewood opener.Highlights include Depp Elem, a smokin Passenger and the Althea> LL Rain> Deal trio, which is  excellent. Set two features a beautiful To Lay Me Down.The jam before the  Wheel is very good with the rest of the set being quite strong. Brent plays some great Moog sounds the entire set. The  encore is missing, drats!
Deep Elem Def one of the better versions of this rarely played tune. Band is on it this night,
Question Is there a way to download these shows or do we just have to listen to them by stream?

Great Show!  Tracking note...... Solid show from start to finish.  Goofy Bobby rap into Playin is supremely entertaining.  A note on the tracking, Baby Blue is located after Deal, so from there on out the tracking is off by one.

wonder These Christmas shows were wonderful. Jerry's fluid playing at this stage of '81 was quite satisfying. It was not duplicated in subsequent years. 
This Passenger would never have been outdone.
The rest of the first set is well played and there is Deep Elem.
The Playing jam is good for this vintage.

81 is 77 Good Revised 12/27/13 - 

I fully agree.  To me, 1981 was the 1977 of the Brent years.  Brent had finally jelled in the band and Jerry hadn't really declined.  Like 1977 and 1974, nearly every show is a good one, and there are some pockets of truly amazing music (see the September Greek run and this NYE run).  

* Note - one thing nobody's mentioned is the over-the-top amazing Looks Like Rain.  IMO Best Evah!

I give this one a 4 only because 9/12/81 and 12/31/81 set a whole new bar for amazingness.

My first show I know the exact moment I became a Deadhead - Bobby turned away from the amps and went to the microphone and sang "I woke today".  I was hooked from that very second and went on to see hundreds of shows, and was lucky enough to work for GDTS.  But I will never forget that one moment in 1981.

JH
